HEADWORD: Thorntail
<hw>Thorn"tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A beautiful South American humming bird (<spn>Gouldia
Popelairii</spn>), having the six outer tail feathers long, slender, and
pointed. The head is ornamented with a long, pointed crest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thorny</ent>⟦br⟧
